        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "If we make a cli call to a php script without using options and using '-' as argument, Zend_Console_Getopt raise a Zend_Console_Getopt_Exception(\"Option \\\"\\\" is not recognized.\") exception.\n\nex: {code}myphpscript.php -{code}\n\nThis is very annoying because it's a standard to use '-' as argument to tell to the script to look at STDIN to get its input.\n\nRegards,\nRemy Damour"
