        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27623",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=remy215",
                        "name": "remy215",
                        "displayName": "Remy Damour",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "as a quick fix, I extended this class, overloading _parseSingleOption method as described below:\n{code}protected function _parseSingleOption($flag, &$argv)\n{\n\tif ($flag === '') return;\n\treturn parent::_parseSingleOption($flag, $argv);\n}{code}\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=remy215",
                        "name": "remy215",
                        "displayName": "Remy Damour",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-23T09:54:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-23T09:54:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27624",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=remy215",
                        "name": "remy215",
                        "displayName": "Remy Damour",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fix on my quick fix :-) (I should have tested first):\nmy quick fix does not generate any error, but ignores \"\\-\" as a remainingArgument, considering it as an option flag: $this->getRemainingArgs() returns an empty array instead of array(\"\\-\");\n\nThe fix below solves all problems (i've highlighted my change). I no longer overload _parseSingleOption() method, but parse() method instead:\n{code}\n    public function parse()\n    {\n        if ($this->_parsed === true) {\n            return;\n        }\n        $argv = $this->_argv;\n        $this->_options = array();\n        $this->_remainingArgs = array();\n        while (count($argv) > 0) {\n            if ($argv[0] == '--') {\n                array_shift($argv);\n                if ($this->_getoptConfig[self::CONFIG_DASHDASH]) {\n                    $this->_remainingArgs = array_merge($this->_remainingArgs, $argv);\n                    break;\n                }\n            }\n            if (substr($argv[0], 0, 2) == '--') {\n                $this->_parseLongOption($argv);\n            } else if ('-' != $argv[0] && substr($argv[0], 0, 1) == '-') {\n                $this->_parseShortOptionCluster($argv);\n            } else {\n                $this->_remainingArgs[] = array_shift($argv);\n            }\n        }\n        $this->_parsed = true;\n        return $this;\n    }\n{code}\n\nchange made is on last \"else if\" statement: } else if ({color:green}'-' != $argv[0] && {color}substr($argv[0], 0, 1) == '-') {\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=remy215",
                        "name": "remy215",
                        "displayName": "Remy Damour",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-23T10:09:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-23T10:09:09.000+0000"
                },
